articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Typhoon Yagi and the landslides and floods it triggered have killed at least 58 people and 40 others are missing in northern Vietnam, the disaster management agency said on Tuesday.
articles.title: Death toll in Vietnam from Typhoon Yagi rises to 58

articles.author: Daniel Fastenberg, Kevin Fogarty, Jarrett Renshaw
articles.description: It is the birthplace of U.S. independence, the "City of Brotherly Love," and the hometown of beloved fictional boxer "Rocky" Balboa.
articles.title: Philadelphia gears up for Harris-Trump debate with protests expected

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russian officials said on Tuesday they shot down at least 15 drones around Moscow overnight in a wave of attacks that set residential buildings on fire, killed a woman and forced more than 30 flights in the capital to be suspended.
articles.title: Ukraine's drones target Moscow, more than 30 airline flights suspended, Russia says

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Israeli airstrikes on a tent camp for displaced Palestinians killed and wounded 65 people in southern Gaza, the enclave's civil emergency service said early on Tuesday, as the Israeli military said it had targeted a Hamas command centre.
articles.title: Dozens killed, wounded in Israeli strikes on Gaza tent camp, Gaza agency says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The United States and China held theatre-level commander talks for the first time on Tuesday, Chinese authorities said, as the two nations look to stabilise military ties and prevent military misunderstandings.
articles.title: Top US, Chinese military officials hold first video call

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The U.S. is set to launch economic talks this week with Bangladesh's interim government, including its leader Nobel Peace Prize laureate Muhammad Yunus, the Financial Times reported on Tuesday.
articles.title: US plans economic talks with Bangladesh's interim leader Muhammad Yunus, FT reports

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Australia said on Tuesday it planned to introduce legislation this year to ban children from using social media platforms, citing the risks it could pose to physical and mental health.
articles.title: Australia plans social media ban for children

articles.author: Subrata Nag Choudhury
articles.description: Junior doctors in India's state of West Bengal vowed on Tuesday to keep up a protest strike over the rape and murder of a trainee doctor unless their demands were met, flouting a Supreme Court deadline.
articles.title: Striking Indian doctors want demands met before returning to work

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: U.S. prosecutors unveiled criminal charges on Monday against two alleged leaders of a white supremacist gang, accusing them of soliciting attacks on Black, Jewish, LGBTQ people and immigrants in hopes of inciting a race war.
articles.title: US charges alleged white supremacist gangsters with trying to incite race war

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: German Interior Minister Nancy Faeser will on Monday announce temporary border controls at all of Germany's land borders, a government source told Reuters.
articles.title: Germany to put temporary controls on all land borders, source says
